                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-113-off583 t18280911-113-crimeloc585"></join>. On the 7th of September, the prisoner came and asked the price of a piece of bacon; I saw her take a piece off the counter and put it about her, into a basket - she then came back to where I stood and offered me half-price for the piece she had asked about: she walked away - I followed and took her about three yards from the door, and found the bacon on her; she begged for mercy.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had the money in my hand - I put the bacon into my basket and he took me directly.</p>
